//Page 06 - Osteochondral Interface

Finding: Trauma - Subchondral Insufficiency Fracture (SIF)//

Given	I'm logged-in with valid credentials
And	I'm on Page 06 -Findings of Knee MRI
When I select the radio button 'Finding'
Then 'Finding' dropdown menu is enabled
When I select 'Trauma - Subchondral Insufficiency Fracture (SIF)' from the Finding dropdown
Then multiple selection Localizer is enabled

And 'Hypointense line-irregular/interrupted' checkbox is enabled
And 'Hypointense area between corticalis & fracture line, "impression of cortical thickening"' checkbox is enabled
And 'Articular surface impression' checkbox is enabled
And 'Corticalis impression' checkbox is enabled
And 'Detection of fluid in the subchondral space' checkbox is enabled
And 'Osteochondral fragment' checkbox is enabled


And 'Bone marrow edema, extensive' checkbox is enabled
And 'Associated meniscal lesion' checkbox is enabled
And 'Location: central in the weight-bearing area' checkbox is enabled

When I select all parts on multiple selection Localizer
Then all parts are selected and turn red

When I select 'Osteochondral fragment' checkbox
Then 'Diameter fragment in mm' input field is enabled
